The paper discusses the development of a framework for automatic topic discovery and query generation for biomedical ontologies using machine learning algorithms. This involves the use of predicate similarity metrics and hierarchical K-means clustering for topic discovery, as well as automatic query generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these are the most relevant areas for the development of machine learning algorithms for topic discovery and query generation. The paper also involves the use of biomedical ontologies, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as these sub-categories are relevant for the management and analysis of large-scale ontologies. Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), as this sub-category is relevant for the development and evaluation of machine learning algorithms.
